headline: TD Earnings: Shares Continue to Look Intriguing after Poor Results
summary: The Toronto-Dominion Bank (TD) (TSE:TD), Canada’s second-largest financial institution with a sizable retail banking operation in the United States, has had a rough year. From a business perspective, the company recently settled an anti-money laundering (AML) violation with the U.S. Department of Justice (DOJ) and has posted poor results.
